The people rejoiced at this, at 9 this freewill offering, contributed without grudging to the Eternal, and David the king was so over­joyed that he blessed the Eter­nal before all the assembly. “Blessed be thou, O Eternal, 10 God of our father Israel,” he
cried, “for ever and for ever.
